description.narrative: For the year 2019, UNICEF support to the nutrition program focused mainly on strengthening the capacity of the health system to deliver quality nutrition services. UNICEF supported the implementation of the policy and strategies to protect, promote and support infant and young child feeding (IYCF) practices. Continued support was provided for the implementation of quality nutrition services, nutrition supply chain management and delivery of behavior change communication (BCC) to address the determinants of under-nutrition through community-based networks. The engagement of adolescents in discussions to understand their health and nutrition issues provided an opportunity for future programming to improve adolescent nutrition. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:10/02/2020
